<paragraph blockId="13.[268,980,781,837]" box="[268,980,813,837]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052">
<heading box="[268,980,813,837]" centered="true" fontSize="36" level="2" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052" reason="7">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Nierstrasz &amp; Brender a Brandis" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[268,510,813,837]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Anathelges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thompsoni">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[268,510,813,837]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052">Anathelges thompsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nierstrasz and Brender à Brandis, 1931)
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="2052" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,243,901,925]" box="[144,243,901,925]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052">
<emphasis box="[144,243,901,925]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,1104,941,1157]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052">
This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thompson" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[488,603,941,965]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Anathelges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyptius">
<emphasis box="[488,507,941,965]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[523,603,941,965]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052">hyptius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the characters of the female, especially the pleotelson, may be juvenile in nature in the only known specimen (but see 
<bibRefCitation author="Markham JC" box="[144,337,1005,1029]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052" pagination="33 - 41" refId="ref6757" refString="Markham JC. 1974. Parasitic bopyrid isopods of the amphi-American genus Stegophryxus Thompson with the description of a new species from California. Bull South Calif Acad Sci. 73: 33 - 41." type="journal article" year="1974">Markham (1974)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Boyko CB &amp; Williams JD" box="[396,718,1005,1029]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052" pagination="795 - 813" refId="ref6336" refString="Boyko CB, Williams JD. 2003. A revision of Anathelges and Stegophryxus (Isopoda: Bopyridae: Athelginae) with descriptions of two new genera and one new species. J Crust Biol. 23: 795 - 813." type="journal article" year="2003">Boyko and Williams (2003))</bibRefCitation>
. The species may be synonymous with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thompson" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[200,312,1037,1061]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Anathelges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyptius">
<emphasis box="[200,219,1037,1061]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[232,312,1037,1061]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052">hyptius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see later) but is in need of redescription based on additional material. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Nierstrasz &amp; Brender a Brandis" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[144,387,1069,1093]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Anathelges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thompsoni">
<emphasis box="[144,387,1069,1093]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052">Anathelges thompsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only been recorded as a single heterosexual pair from the 
<typeStatus box="[144,192,1101,1125]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<collectingRegion box="[333,457,1101,1125]" country="Chile" name="Valparaiso" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052">Valparaiso</collectingRegion>
in central 
<collectingCountry box="[590,650,1101,1125]" name="Chile" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052">Chile</collectingCountry>
infesting an unidentified pagurid host (Nierstrasz and Brender à Brandis 1931; 
<bibRefCitation author="Boyko CB &amp; Williams JD" box="[604,901,1133,1157]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2052" pagination="795 - 813" refId="ref6336" refString="Boyko CB, Williams JD. 2003. A revision of Anathelges and Stegophryxus (Isopoda: Bopyridae: Athelginae) with descriptions of two new genera and one new species. J Crust Biol. 23: 795 - 813." type="journal article" year="2003">Boyko and Williams 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
